The MIT permission notice for the alfred foundation is reproduced in the
LICENSE file at the root of this repository and applies to the foundation
code in full.

The alfred foundation was published to PyPI as `alfred-vault` and is
available at https://github.com/ssdavidai/alfred. Algernon is a friendly,
disclosed fork of that project. Both trees have since diverged and are
developed independently; Algernon does not track a live upstream.

The Algernon platform — the multi-instance architecture, the peer/transport
protocol, per-instance scope enforcement, and the additional subsystems
documented in ATTRIBUTION.md — is original work by Andrew Newton, built on
top of the alfred foundation and distributed under the same MIT terms.

See ATTRIBUTION.md for a module-level map of which subsystems originate in
the alfred foundation and which are Algernon-original.
